The umbrella is a hybrid between a shield and a cannon that gets a hefty boost from height advantage. It’s easily overwhelmed by creeper waves though, and has a few other caveats.
I publish videos daily, like and subscribe!
title: Custom Unit Demo: Umbrella, by qople | Creeper World 4 Colonies #232

Description of this map:
An old field of sports becomes a battlefield. Where once fairness & victory have been, you find a vicious enemy & omens of early defeat.
Can you win? And how long will this ‘game’ last..?
This is somewhat a tribute to a map of Dark Reign back from the ’90s, but as there are already some “straight forward” maps in the exchange, i ended with a totally different approach and a siege setup.

title: Chicago Duty 1 - Career 5 | 911 Operator

contents:
Description of this map:
The first level in the series to have 4RPL units. Here you find a fort with damaged walls, several valleys with creeper breeder, crystal towers, and totems, and also there is three spore towers and a single emitter. One of the spore tower targets the greenar mother in particular. There are also a few AC temples and a bunch of bluite.

One’s here right now, reading, thinking. “Should I sell my soul to this friendly devil? He’s so trustworthy after all. What’s a flimsy little sniper compared to the creeper menace?”
Do it. Sign. Sign the contract. Do it.
